"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-24-Esports-joins-the-Olympics-Inside-the-2-4bn-industry-1wj9kCsE7g4-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  The Agenda  Copied  Esports \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 or competitive gaming \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 is the latest member of the Olympic family. Following the first ever World Cup of esports \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 taking place right now in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, this time next year the inaugural Esports Olympics will take place in the same city.  Esports is already worth $2.4 billion annually, and it's predicted to grow by 20 percent per year. So what is behind that growth? How does it all work? And what do you need to do to become a world-class competitive gamer?  In this edition ofThe Agenda, Juliet Mann speaks toRalf Reichert, Chief Executive of the Esports World Cup Foundation;Mario Ho, Co-founder and Co-CEO of NIP Group, the first Chinese Esports company to list on the NASDAQ stock exchange; andJake Trotman, competitive gamer and Assistant Lecturer in Esports business at the University of Salford.  FIND MORE STORIES FROMTHE AGENDAHERE  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"